# Collapsible Sidebar Docs

## Overview
Better documentation navigation. Collapsible sidebar layout. Toggle button. Smooth transitions. Mobile-responsive with hamburger menu. Active section highlighting. Better UX for reading docs.

## Technical Approach
New layout component for docs. Sidebar state managed in component state. Toggle button collapses/expands sidebar. CSS transitions for smooth animation. Mobile breakpoint shows hamburger menu. Active route highlighted.

## User Stories

### US-001: Create Collapsible Sidebar Layout
**Priority:** 1
**Maven Steps:** [5, 10]
**MCP Tools:** []

As a documentation reader, I want a collapsible sidebar so that I can maximize reading space.

**Acceptance Criteria:**
- Docs layout component created
- Sidebar collapses/expanded
- Toggle button in header
- Smooth CSS transitions
- State persists in localStorage
- Typecheck passes

**Status:** false

### US-002: Implement Mobile Menu
**Priority:** 1
**Maven Steps:** [5, 10]
**MCP Tools:** []

As a mobile user, I want a hamburger menu so that I can access docs navigation on small screens.

**Acceptance Criteria:**
- Hamburger menu on mobile (<768px)
- Menu opens sidebar as overlay
- Click outside to close
- Backdrop blur effect
- Typecheck passes

**Status:** false

### US-003: Highlight Active Section
**Priority:** 1
**Maven Steps:** [5, 10]
**MCP Tools:** []

As a documentation reader, I want the active section highlighted so that I know where I am.

**Acceptance Criteria:**
- Active route highlighted in sidebar
- Different background color
- Bold text
- Scrolled into view if needed
- Typecheck passes

**Status:** false

### US-004: Define Sidebar Structure
**Priority:** 1
**Maven Steps:** [5]
**MCP Tools:** []

As a documentation reader, I want organized sidebar sections so that I can find topics easily.

**Acceptance Criteria:**
- Sidebar sections: Getting Started, Database, Authentication, Realtime, Storage, GraphQL, SDK, MCP Integration
- Nested items where appropriate
- Collapsible sections
- Typecheck passes

**Status:** false

### US-005: Add Smooth Transitions
**Priority:** 2
**Maven Steps:** [5, 10]
**MCP Tools:** []

As a documentation reader, I want smooth transitions so that the UI feels polished.

**Acceptance Criteria:**
- CSS transition on sidebar width
- Duration: 300ms
- Easing function
- Content area adjusts smoothly
- Typecheck passes

**Status:** false

### US-006: Persist Sidebar State
**Priority:** 2
**Maven Steps:** [5, 10]
**MCP Tools:** []

As a documentation reader, I want sidebar state remembered so that it stays how I left it.

**Acceptance Criteria:**
- State saved to localStorage
- State restored on page load
- Default: expanded on desktop, collapsed on mobile
- Typecheck passes

**Status:** false

### US-007: Add Keyboard Shortcut
**Priority:** 3
**Maven Steps:** [5, 10]
